    <name>Pro Tips: Building Communities for Learning</name>
    <intro></intro>
    <introformat>1</introformat>
    <content>&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Key%20Idea.png" alt="" width="140" height="136" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_middle"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use case based-learning:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;To introduce or conclude an instructional topic, adults may be engaged&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;by a relevant situation&amp;nbsp;(case) because they can&amp;nbsp;then analyze that case to identify and practice&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;applying potential&amp;nbsp;solutions (study).&amp;nbsp;We are using captioned video, along with access to a&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;transcript, to support variability in all learners whatever their context.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Because they are real-life examples, case&amp;nbsp;studies that include multiple options for&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;perception&amp;nbsp; further optimize&amp;nbsp;relevance, value, and authenticity. (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Engagement&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Principle: UDL&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement/recruiting-interest/relevance-value-authenticity" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 7.2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Base&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;adult learning in real world concerns&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Involve adults in solving problems related to their&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;own practice to optimize for relevance, value, and authenticity. For example, if the goal is to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;teach adults to use a new data graphing tool, you might ask adults with health concerns to track&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;their water intake or the number of walked steps. Similarly, if you were teaching them to learn a&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;new interpersonal skill, you might ask&amp;nbsp;them to re-enact scenarios they have encountered in their&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;work environments where the skill would prove useful (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/representation" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Representation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/representation/comprehension/background-knowledge" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Checkpoint&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-contrast="auto" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;3.1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Everyone wants to be a valuable member of a winning team doing important work:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Recognizing&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;this about your learners, colleagues, and community members can enhance the way learning and&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;growth are approached. For example, if maintaining a safe learning environment is an established&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;classroom goal, the important work is to create a&amp;nbsp;sense of belonging. Winning then becomes the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;reality of a classroom where all learners feel safe to engage and share. Finally, remind learners&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;they are doing important work – learning – that will have a significant positive impact on their&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;life. (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="font-size: 1.7rem; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Engagement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement/effort-persistence/collaboration-community" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="font-size: 1.7rem; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 8.3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Run an accessibility checker:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Many authoring tools now include a built-in accessibility checker.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;This is the case with Microsoft Word, and your learning management system may also include a&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;built-in checker. Like a spelling and grammar checker, the accessibility checker will not catch all&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;accessibility issues, but it will give you a good idea of the biggest ones the checker can reliably&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;identify. More important than focusing on just the identified errors, make sure to review the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;guidance if it is available. This will help you understand why each error is important to address&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;and the steps for doing so. By reading this guidance you can help your accessibility skills over&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;time (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/action-expression" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="font-size: 1.7rem; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Action &amp;amp; Expression&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/action-expression/physical-action/assistive-technologies" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="font-size: 1.7rem; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 4.2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use lists to focus social media use:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;While there are many benefits to building a robust&amp;nbsp; PLN,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;many educators shy away from using social media for their professional learning out of a fear&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;that it may take too much time or result in information overload. However, with a few simple&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;strategies social media can be used effectively for professional development in adult&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;education.&amp;nbsp; One strategy is to use the list feature available on platforms such as X (Twitter) to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;provide a more focused view of the posts shared on the timeline (the stream of posts from&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;everyone you follow and some that are selected by the platform based on your interests).&amp;nbsp; For&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;example, you might create a list of national organizations, and another one for agencies in your&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;state you want to follow. (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/action-expression" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Action &amp;amp; Expression&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/action-expression/executive-functions/information-resources/information-resources" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 6.3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/divider%20wave.png" alt="" width="1920" height="195" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_text-bottom"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
